        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>In this science goal, we will conduct a spectral line survey from 336 GHz to 363 GHz with Band 7.  

As for the correlator setting, we choose the band width of 1875.0 MHz with the dual polarization mode, which gives us the frequency resolution of 1.129 MHz corresponding to 1.0 km/s at 349.5 GHz.  Since the typical line width is 3 km/s in the CMM3 region, this resolution is enough to study the velocity structure. 

The expected resolution of 0.4", which corresponds to 295 AU at 738 pc, can spatially resolve the hot core.  Even if the size of hot core is comparable to the size of SMA continuum peak (~3"), the maximum angular scale of 5.2" is enough to observe the hot core without missing flux.

According to our ASTE observation, the CH3OH (12_1 - 12_0$ A$-+; 336.865110 GHz)is detected with the peak intensity of 0.17 K.  This line is one of the faintest line with the upper state energy of &gt; 150 K detected in our ASTE survey.  If the hot core size of 5" is assumed, the expected peak intensity of the CH3OH line is expected to be 3.3 K, because the beam size of ASTE observation is 22".  This corresponds to 49 mJy with the 0.4" resolution.  After the 15 minutes of on-source-time integration, the rms noise level of 4.8 mJy can be achieved with the frequency resolution of 1.129 MHz.  With this sensitivity, we can obtain the CH_3OH map with a reasonable S/N ratio of 10 sigma or higher.  Considering the overheads for various calibrations, overaheads, and 4 frequency settings, we request 4.4 hours of the observation time to complete the program. </prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
